Round 1: 
[Patient] How much water should I drink daily to manage my heart failure? 
[Educator] Aim for 8-10 cups of water a day to stay hydrated and help your heart.

Round 2:
[Patient] Can I drink other fluids besides water to stay hydrated? 
[Educator] Yes, you can also have low-sugar juices, herbal teas, and clear broths.

Round 3:
[Patient] Are there any fluids I should avoid to prevent fluid overload? 
[Educator] Limit intake of sodas, energy drinks, and salty soups to avoid excess fluid retention.

Round 4:
[Patient] How can I track my daily fluid intake to make sure I'm staying within limits? 
[Educator] Try using a water bottle with measurements or keeping a journal to track your intake.

Round 5:
[Patient] Should I drink more water when I'm feeling short of breath? 
[Educator] Yes, increasing water intake can help thin mucus and ease breathing during shortness of breath.